## Amazon EKS (Elastic Kubernetes Service)

**Amazon EKS** is AWS's **managed Kubernetes service**.

### Simple Definition

> **EKS lets you run and manage Kubernetes clusters on AWS.**

---

## Example

```text
Docker App
     │
Kubernetes
     │
Amazon EKS
     │
Runs Containers
```

---

## Why use EKS?

- ✅ Run Kubernetes applications
- ✅ Auto Scaling
- ✅ High Availability
- ✅ AWS manages the Kubernetes control plane
- ✅ Works with Docker containers

---

## ECS vs EKS

| ECS                              | EKS                           |
| -------------------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| AWS's own container service      | Managed Kubernetes service    |
| Easier to learn                  | More complex                  |
| AWS-specific                     | Portable across clouds        |
| No Kubernetes knowledge required | Requires Kubernetes knowledge |

---

## When to use?

- **ECS** → If you're only using AWS and want a simpler container service.
- **EKS** → If your application already uses Kubernetes or needs to run across multiple cloud providers.

---

## Interview (1 line)

> **Amazon EKS is a managed Kubernetes service that simplifies deploying, managing, and scaling containerized applications on AWS.**

### Easy way to remember

- **Docker** → Packages your app.
- **ECS** → AWS manages Docker containers.
- **EKS** → AWS manages Kubernetes clusters.
- **Kubernetes** → Manages containers across many servers.

